pageContext.description: Dimensions: EL 54.5mm; EBm 29; Blp 7; Wt. 44.8 g,Typology: triple m-m, but lower most one on face only; reasonably crisp body angles with only sl. bowed face and side sections; evidently had a slender, virt. parallel body; long asym. rel. to cg. flash,Manufacture: sl. remains of cg. flash; thickness of body wall on face at lower break suggests sl. misplaced core, causing over-thin opposite face? rough bumb 6mm long on socket inside - a casting defect.,Condition: breaks all dirty and pres. ancient; modern scoremark to left of loop; metal relatively thin down break at body angle - ?weak point causing break.,Attached Material: yellow-brown soil traces all over.
pageContext.surface: Fragments of dull green patina intact - very thin layer, mostly flaked to coarser light green surface; few corners and edges little chipped to pale bluey-green dusty surface.
pageContext.collection: Streeter, Mr. Brian J. S. - private (1981),23 Windmill Road, West Croydon
